oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Melba Hotel
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the exterior of the Melba Hotel, formerly located in Jackson. There are various advertisements on the side of the building for Dr. Pepper, James Shoe Hospital, and Coca-Cola. People can be seen walking on the sidewalk and in the street.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Hotels; Automobiles; Advertisements
